<br>
We are awesome soloers and raiders so if we totally and clearly owned groups too would that honestly be fair with 14 classes in the game?<br>
<br>
Where the caster classes have an innate advantage is that if we dont recruit a tank we dont need a healer either. We can fill our whole group with caster dps and a support or two. And many do, though invites to all caster groups are *very* much based on reputation in my experience. They are incredible xp but they carry high risk too, especially if no resser, though usually someone has one boxed <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
eg. I got invited to a 4 mage, enc(, wiz=me) group this week which was great fun. Afaik there arent any 4 mnk, enc, rog groups any more.<br>
<br>
There *used* to be that kind of group with the wussy luclin mobs (though it would prob be shaman rather than enc) but SoE put a stop to that with PoP, and some melee are still peeved they cant solo/duo/do non-trinity groups like we can. That's prob the main drive for extending the blue range again. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=pilsainsilverback>Pilsain Silverback</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Arcanist</span><br>  Posts: 961<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 8:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Bottom line on grouping today (no flames or whining)</span><hr size=1> I'm speaking as a casual player in a casual guild, at level 51.<br>
<br>
I have NO problems getting groups.  Now, if I run around with the LFG tag on, I rarely get invites.  However, people want to group.  So, I just start soliciting people to group.  In most places other than PoP, you don't need a tank, or a cleric, if you have the right mix (and the people who believe the same).  You really only need a cleric if you have a warrior (even though having one is always nice).<br>
<br>
We recently grouped in Dulak, killing dk blues, with me, two clerics, a ranger, a bard, and a rogue.  I also had a group (which was awesome) of me, two druids, two rangers, and a shaman.  I could barely cast IC twice before the mobs were dead.  <br>
<br>
Both of those groups were pick-ups (me and one ranger were guildies), and I had very little problem in getting them together. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=rombusmindspire>Rombus Mindspire</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><table width=111><tr><td style=filter:glow(color=#6633FF strength=1);font-family:arial;font-weight;bold;font-size:'1pt' nowrap><font size=1 color=#FFFFFF face=Verdana, Arial, Helvetica, sans-serif>Forum Tyrant<br><br>Owned by Ikeya<BR>Destroying EverWars...<BR><a href=mailto:rombus@graffe.com style=text-decoration: none><u>Contact Rombus</u></font></td></tr></table></span><br>  Posts: 7321<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 8:37 am)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> I've said it a thousand times before and I'll say it a thousand times again... it's all perception.  Hopefully visual damage will help us out in this department. <p><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE CENTER START--><div style="text-align:center"><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.tritonguild.com/rombus/sig.gif"/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="font-family:Verdana;font-size:xx-small;">Officer of Triton, Member of Team Ice, Povar<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=458434" target="top">Rombus, Arcanist</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--> .:. <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=5702" target="top">Rommy, Archon<