<br>
First off, strange as it sounds, in an XP situation in tier 3 and lower a ranger can tank just fine (I have a 65 ranger as a tank alot, and they have no problems tanking with NO elemental gear - that includes mobs like Gaukr and his brothers in lower BoT).<br>
<br>
Secondly, hot keys are your friend.  A root and stun hot key that announces to the group you are saving the chanter/shaman/cleric from death by said action makes you more visible.  Our stun lands better than a chanters, and if nothing else will usually pull aggro off said person, giving your group time to recover.  Do it enough and you WILL end up on peoples mental list of 'People to Group With'.  <br>
<br>
Sure, aggro is seen as our downfall by some, but with some creativity it can be a tool to your advantage.<br>
<br>
As far as improvements, I would LOVE for flappy to affect my group.  That is easily the best improvement that would address group desirability for wizards.<br>
