<br>
Example, my group was hunting Vamps in the castle in Tenebrous Mountains. One of the named ones is a wizard that casts ice comet. He managed to get two full ice comets on the SK and down he went. <br>
<br>
The next day, me and the SK were hunting together, and talked about the night before. He pointed out that the wizard vamp could nuke for 1120, and that my nukes where smaller. I told him, I wasn't using the same spells, because two DoF did more damage then one ice comet in the same time. (I have ID3, Robe of Tempest).<br>
<br>
So, I loaded ice comet and showed him (Hit for 1140) and he was all, dam! The next mob I used two draughts of fire, and hit for 688 and 708. When he found out that for 430 mana, I did 1396 damage compared to 1140 for 400, he saw the difference.<br>
<br>
But from his point of view, ice comet was still better, cause it delivered over 1k damage all at once. And when I crit with ice comet for 18k (Love ID3) at level 52, people just say that is unfair. <br>
<br>
I was good at not getting aggro before I had concussion, and now with it, I'm even better. In fact, on the same hunting trip, when our tank got iced (ha ha) a monk broke the mezz on a corertie general (Whole seperat issue), and the other melees had trouble pulling it off the enchanter. I over nuked, on purpose, got aggro and the concussioned it off me. <br>
<br>
We all laughed afterwards, because in the past, the enchanter has saved our group many many times, and this time, the tables where turned on him. <br>
<br>
Not to say wizards don't have issues. There is something to the arguement that in the high end game, other classes outside of tank/heal/slow/crowd control can bring good DPS and more. <br>
<br>
Perhaps wizards do need something now to offer a group. Personally, I'm not to interested in being a buffing class. There have been many ideas posted on here, some of which I think could work with out overpowering, or stepping on others toes. It's been suggested that some of the effects from our familiar also effect our group. I'm sure that if the resists our familars give us were partially given to the group, they would like that very much, since they raise all resists, and are stackable. It could be an AA ability.<br>
<br>
Group Harvest would be usefull as well, since healers would love an instant shot of mana, enough to give someone that CH. <br>
<br>
One idea that came to me recently, if we really wanted a buff, was one that allowed us to improve anyones weapon damage. The only thing about it would be that some might feel it was more of an enchanters spells. But the idea would be that we could cause a weapon to burst into flames (or magic or ice) which would increase the damage, lower the delay, and add a fire, cold,magic damage bonus. We all know, melees love anything that makes them fight better, faster, and do more damage. Even at if the spell at best raised damage, say 7-10, lowered delay 2-4, and gave a fire,cold,magic bonus of +4, it wouldn't be over powering, so long as it would last a few minutes, and had a fast cast time, and low mana cost, so it doesn't eat to much into mana used for nuking.  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=faramir42>Faramir42</A> at: 6/19/03 10:12 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jayteebushwacker>Jaytee Bushwacker</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 162<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 10:14 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> If you can see melee damage numbers you should see caster non-melee damage as well.  Conflicting standards always aggrivated me in this game.  If *I* can see my damage why the hell cant joe shmoe sitting next to me notice OMFG that thing just blew up for 3500 dmg!<br>
