<br>
- Im finding grouping to definitely be more profitable xp-wise, so that was good<br>
- widening the level range so that things dont turn light blue and green so fast was good<br>
- Im finding groups in PoP to be even harder to come by, so this is bad. Also the quality of groups has gone down, and get my ass killed more. I think maybe they should have made the minimum level for PoV/PoS 60 or 61 for people who dont have the flag, and higher for higher tiers.<br>
- Im finding soloing to be less profitable xp-wise in PoP but more profitable elsewhere, but only relative to the way it was. PoP xp still blows previous expansion zones xp away and at 65 it is a waste of ones time to go anywhere else, so I feel this change was unnecessary and irritating.<br>
- what they should have done instead was maybe increase some ZEMs on a few older zones, maybe toughened them up a bit too, or parts of them. The underlying issues with ZEMs which they havent really spoken about is the huge amount of xp that is needed for lvls 61-65, which I suspect was the reason for the original ZEMs in PoP in the first place.<br>
<br>
But thats just my opinion, I could be wrong. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=mookus>Mookus</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 161<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 10:48 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: re:</span><hr size=1> Im posting this so low on the thread, so i doubt it'll get much read but... <br>
<br>
It's my opinion that wizards have historically been the way they are because of what they used to be before kunark. Way back before group aggregate damage.<br>
<br>
Back then, as many will recall, it wasn't the group that did the most damage that got credit for the kill. It was the group that had the person who did the most damage that got the kill.<br>
<br>
One wiz could KS entire groups, easily. By doing as little as 20% damage for instance.<br>
<br>
<br>
Because of this... wizards were highly desired to be in your group. Because we were the insurance that some famous ks'er couldn't come steal your kills, exp and loot. Those were fun times i might add.<br>
<br>
The thing is, a lot of people made wizards. To many people in fact that healthy balance wasn't there. <br>
<br>
At first verant limited the wizard's power to prevent him from being able to KS groups so easily. And secondly, they made other classes better to encourage the better balance of classes they had envisioned.<br>
<br>
Eventually, group aggregte damage was put in place, and the number one reason i was always snatched up into groups immediately went poof instantly.<br>
<br>
But it still took them a few years to round out the wizard class. I guess the fear of wizzies was still well entrenched on the mindsets of the game's designers for a while. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub140.ezboard.com/bgraffeswizardcompilation.showUserPublicProfile?gid=fqubedf3povar>FqubedF3povar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Channeler</span><br>  Posts: 181<br> <font color=#ffffff>(6/19/03 10:57 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: grouping</span><hr size=1> I dont know if its due to vidual caster dmg or whatever but after the patch ive gotten ALOT more groups, ive not gone lfg for more then 5 mins and not gotten a tell, a bit frustrating waiting for a raid and turning down groups but i digress. <br>
